const L = [
["Maslow's Hierarchy","Maslow proposed in 1943 that human needs form a pyramid. Base: physiological needs—food, water, shelter. Second: safety. Third: love and belonging. Fourth: esteem. Top: self-actualization. Lower needs must be met before higher ones. Criticism: too rigid, doesn't account for cultural differences.","马斯洛1943年提出人类需求呈金字塔。底部：生理需求。第二层：安全。第三层：爱和归属。第四层：尊重。顶部：自我实现。低层需求须先满足。批评：过于僵化，未考虑文化差异。",[{q:"When was this proposed?",a:"1923",b:"1933",c:"1943",d:"1953",ans:"C",exp:"1943年提出。"},{q:"Top of the pyramid?",a:"Esteem",b:"Self-actualization",c:"Love",d:"Safety",ans:"B",exp:"自我实现。"},{q:"Criticism of the theory?",a:"Too simple",b:"Doesn't account for cultural differences",c:"Focuses on lower needs",d:"Invalid research",ans:"B",exp:"未考虑文化差异。"}]],
["Public Speaking","Five principles: 1) Preparation—research, organize, practice. 2) Know your audience—tailor your message. 3) Manage anxiety—deep breathing, visualization, positive self-talk. 4) Body language—eye contact, natural gestures, purposeful movement. 5) Engage your audience—stories, examples, questions. Speeches that feel like conversations are most effective.","五个原则：1）准备——研究、组织、练习。2）了解听众——量身定制。3）管理焦虑——深呼吸、可视化、积极自我对话。4）肢体语言——眼神交流、自然手势。5）吸引听众——故事、例子、问题。感觉像对话的演讲最有效。",[{q:"First principle?",a:"Know audience",b:"Manage anxiety",c:"Preparation",d:"Body language",ans:"C",exp:"第一个原则是准备。"},{q:"Anxiety management techniques?",a:"Coffee",b:"Deep breathing, visualization, positive self-talk",c:"Avoid eye contact",d:"Speak quickly",ans:"B",exp:"深呼吸、可视化和积极自我对话。"},{q:"What makes speech effective?",a:"Complex vocabulary",b:"Loud voice",c:"Feels like a conversation",d:"Statistical data",ans:"C",exp:"感觉像对话的演讲更有效。"}]],
["Supply and Demand","Law of demand: price rises, quantity demanded falls. Law of supply: price rises, quantity supplied increases. Equilibrium: supply equals demand. Above equilibrium: surplus. Below equilibrium: shortage. Understanding these dynamics is crucial for market analysis.","需求法则：价格上涨，需求量下降。供给法则：价格上涨，供给量增加。均衡：供给等于需求。高于均衡：过剩。低于均衡：短缺。理解这些动态对市场分析至关重要。",[{q:"When price rises, demand?",a:"Increases",b:"Decreases",c:"Stays same",d:"Random",ans:"B",exp:"价格上涨需求量下降。"},{q:"Equilibrium price is where?",a:"Highest price",b:"Lowest price",c:"Supply equals demand",d:"Average price",ans:"C",exp:"供给等于需求。"},{q:"Below equilibrium causes?",a:"Surplus",b:"Shortage",c:"Stability",d:"More production",ans:"B",exp:"短缺。"}]],
["Effective Learning Strategies","Research shows several strategies improve learning. Spaced repetition—reviewing material at increasing intervals—outperforms cramming. Active recall—testing yourself—strengthens memory more than re-reading. The Pomodoro Technique—25 minutes focused work plus 5-minute breaks—maintains concentration. Teaching others (the Feynman Technique) deepens understanding. Sleep consolidation means studying before sleep improves retention.","研究表明几种策略改善学习。间隔重复优于突击复习。主动回忆比重读更能增强记忆。番茄工作法保持专注。教别人（费曼技巧）加深理解。睡眠巩固意味着睡前学习改善记忆保持。",[{q:"What outperforms cramming?",a:"Re-reading",b:"Spaced repetition",c:"Highlighting",d:"Summarizing",ans:"B",exp:"间隔重复优于突击复习。"},{q:"Active recall means?",a:"Re-reading notes",b:"Testing yourself",c:"Highlighting text",d:"Making outlines",ans:"B",exp:"主动回忆是测试自己。"},{q:"Feynman Technique involves?",a:"Studying alone",b:"Teaching others",c:"Memorizing formulas",d:"Taking notes",ans:"B",exp:"教别人加深理解。"}]],
["Cross-Cultural Communication","Effective cross-cultural communication requires awareness of cultural differences in communication styles. High-context cultures (Japan, China) rely on implicit messages and context. Low-context cultures (US, Germany) prefer direct, explicit communication. Nonverbal cues—gestures, eye contact, personal space—vary significantly across cultures. Active listening, avoiding assumptions, and asking clarifying questions are essential skills for cross-cultural interactions.","有效的跨文化沟通需要意识到文化差异。高语境文化（日本、中国）依赖隐含信息和语境。低语境文化（美国、德国）偏好直接明确的沟通。非语言信号——手势、眼神、个人空间——在不同文化中差异很大。积极倾听、避免假设和询问澄清问题是跨文化交流的必备技能。",[{q:"High-context cultures rely on?",a:"Direct speech",b:"Implicit messages and context",c:"Written communication",d:"Formal language",ans:"B",exp:"高语境文化依赖隐含信息和语境。"},{q:"Low-context cultures prefer?",a:"Indirect hints",b:"Silence",c:"Direct, explicit communication",d:"Gestures only",ans:"C",exp:"低语境文化偏好直接明确的沟通。"},{q:"Important cross-cultural skill?",a:"Speaking loudly",b:"Using jargon",c:"Active listening and asking clarifying questions",d:"Avoiding eye contact",ans:"C",exp:"积极倾听和询问澄清问题。"}]],
];

